title: UPDATE OFF NORMAL: PRV popped on overpressure * Re: LI20 poly tank alarming per Security. LI20 ACS surge tank indicates water leak
text: CEFOM Gonzalez reports that a "PRV" (pressure relieving valve) on the system had opened, relieving an over-pressure on the system (as designed to do). Gonzalez found that a bypass line had been closed, probably by some workers installing a water system in housing earlier. Once the bypass was opened, the pressure went back down and the PRV re-seated itself shut. CEFOM will followup on Saturday with workers in area
